Had you any conversation with them? - They asked me where I had been to; I said to the Broadway to get some Gin, but there was nobody up;
Gypsy George
said, if we would go along with him, we should have some Gin; we went home to his house.

Did you give him another blow? - No;
Benjamin Harley
and Henman gave him a blow each, I gave him none, and whether the prisoner did or no, I cannot say.

"and groaned;
Gypsy George
said, Come up,

I keep the Ship alehouse: Potter came to my house for help; I went with him directly; I laid hold of the two Cunninghams, Clarke got off in the mean time; I sent directly for an officer to secure them;
Bet Cunningham
gave me a guinea and a shilling out of her hand; I found one guinea in a pail of suds; the dollar was found under the bed; Clarke made her escape, but was afterwards taken.
